It seems like new ice cream places are popping up in the area all the time but what you actually want on any given day is Colleen's. No lavender rose water coconut based BS here. This is the ice cream you had after ball games, school concerts and whenever you earned a celebration (doesn't matter if you grew up somewhere else [I did]--every place has a great shop like this) and it's actually as good as you remember! They also have grill items which I haven't had but look and smell delicious. And considering every kid was eating a grilled cheese when I went midday once, I would say it's a good one too.

Ice cream 10/10 Frappes 10/10 Service & decor 10/10  I personally ordered two scoops of their salted caramel truffle mixed with their vanilla. It was some of the best salted caramel I've ever had. The flavor was rich and sweet yet ultimately light on the palette. My friend had the salted caramel topped with fudge, and the fudge was also packed full of chocolate flavor with a deeper hint of something else that we couldn't place. Very delicious. Lastly, my other friend ordered their strawberry frappe. The same situation: concentrated yet natural flavor, thick in texture like a frappe should be but not overpowering.  The service was great. They were really patient and easygoing. The decor was a trip back into the 50's. Very retro-diner-ish but not overly garish. We sat and ate; the atmosphere invited you to sit in peace and have a chat. It was busy but not overly loud. All in all, this place is a gem. Can't wait to go back again.
